external_knowledge:
- 'Owner' refers to the user who is primarily responsible for the model;
- 'Top feature' is the feature with the highest importance in the model;
- 'Accuracy' is a common performance metric used to evaluate the effectiveness of a model in machine learning.

- 'Linear Regression' is a type of predictive modeling technique used in statistics and machine learning to understand the relationship between a dependent variable and one or more independent variables.;
- 'R^2' (R-squared) is a statistical measure that represents the proportion of the variance for a dependent variable that's explained by an independent variable or variables in a regression model.;
- A higher R^2 value (closer to 1) indicates a better fit of the model to the data.;
- 'Public' datasets are accessible to the general public and can be used for various analyses and model training.;
- 'Artisans' in this context refers to data scientists or users who have created models.

- A model in this context refers to a machine learning model;
- The `importance` column indicates the significance of each feature in the model, with higher values indicating more important features;
- The `dataset_id` is a unique identifier linking datasets to models.

- 'Gardens blooming with more than five flowers' refers to datasets with more than 5 features;
- 'Gardener has used a linear regression model to predict the growth' refers to the presence of at least one model of the 'Linear Regression' type;
- 'Average mean of features' refers to the mean value of the features;
- 'RMSE' is a performance metric used to evaluate the accuracy of the linear regression model.

- 'Cumulative accuracy' refers to the sum of performance metric values over time for each model.;
- 'Best model' is determined by the highest cumulative accuracy.;
- 'Latest evaluations' means the most recent evaluation dates are considered.;

- "Top performers" refers to models with the highest performance metrics;
- "Fragrant blossoms" and "accumulate their scent" refer to the cumulative performance metrics of the top three models;
- "Plot of land" refers to the dataset ID;
- "Gardener" refers to the user ID;
- "Average size of the soil" refers to the average file size of the datasets;
- "Number of plants" refers to the number of models per dataset.

- "shining stars" refers to the top-performing models;
- "pinnacle of their respective datasets" means the models with the highest metric value for each dataset;
- "brought them to the stage" refers to the users who uploaded the datasets.

sql:
SELECT 
  (SELECT COUNT(model_id) FROM models) AS total_models,
  (SELECT COUNT(user_id) FROM users) AS total_users;
